instructions:
## Add Recharts to Next.js

### 1. Install Recharts
- Run: `npm install recharts`.
- TypeScript types are bundled — do NOT install `@types/recharts`.
- Verify: `node_modules/recharts` exists.

### 2. SSR-safe wrapper (REQUIRED)
- Recharts accesses the browser `window` object internally. You MUST mark every file that imports from `recharts` as a Client Component.
- Add `'use client';` at the top of every chart component file.
- Alternatively, lazy-load chart components with `next/dynamic` and `{ ssr: false }` to keep them out of the server bundle entirely:
  ```tsx
  import dynamic from 'next/dynamic';
  const RevenueChart = dynamic(() => import('@/components/charts/revenue-chart'), { ssr: false });
  ```
- For Server Components that need charts, fetch data server-side and pass it as props to a Client Component child.

### 3. ResponsiveContainer (always required)
- Every Recharts chart MUST be wrapped in `<ResponsiveContainer>`. Without it, charts render at 0×0 inside flex/grid layouts.
- Always set `width="100%"` and a fixed `height` in pixels:
  ```tsx
  'use client';
  import { ResponsiveContainer, LineChart, Line, XAxis, YAxis, CartesianGrid, Tooltip } from 'recharts';

  export function RevenueChart({ data }: { data: { month: string; revenue: number }[] }) {
    return (
      <ResponsiveContainer width="100%" height={300}>
        <LineChart data={data} margin={{ top: 5, right: 20, left: 0, bottom: 5 }}>
          <CartesianGrid strokeDasharray="3 3" />
          <XAxis dataKey="month" />
          <YAxis />
          <Tooltip />
          <Line type="monotone" dataKey="revenue" stroke="#6366f1" strokeWidth={2} dot={false} />
        </LineChart>
      </ResponsiveContainer>
    );
  }
  ```

### 4. Bar chart
```tsx
'use client';
import { ResponsiveContainer, BarChart, Bar, XAxis, YAxis, CartesianGrid, Tooltip, Legend } from 'recharts';

export function SignupsChart({ data }: { data: { week: string; signups: number; churns: number }[] }) {
  return (
    <ResponsiveContainer width="100%" height={300}>
      <BarChart data={data}>
        <CartesianGrid strokeDasharray="3 3" />
        <XAxis dataKey="week" />
        <YAxis />
        <Tooltip />
        <Legend />
        <Bar dataKey="signups" fill="#6366f1" />
        <Bar dataKey="churns" fill="#ef4444" />
      </BarChart>
    </ResponsiveContainer>
  );
}
```

### 5. Area chart (for cumulative trends)
```tsx
'use client';
import { ResponsiveContainer, AreaChart, Area, XAxis, YAxis, CartesianGrid, Tooltip } from 'recharts';

export function MRRChart({ data }: { data: { month: string; mrr: number }[] }) {
  return (
    <ResponsiveContainer width="100%" height={300}>
      <AreaChart data={data}>
        <CartesianGrid strokeDasharray="3 3" />
        <XAxis dataKey="month" />
        <YAxis tickFormatter={(v) => `$${v}`} />
        <Tooltip formatter={(v: number) => [`$${v}`, 'MRR']} />
        <Area type="monotone" dataKey="mrr" stroke="#6366f1" fill="#6366f150" strokeWidth={2} />
      </AreaChart>
    </ResponsiveContainer>
  );
}
```

### 6. Pie chart
```tsx
'use client';
import { ResponsiveContainer, PieChart, Pie, Cell, Tooltip } from 'recharts';

const COLORS = ['#6366f1', '#8b5cf6', '#06b6d4', '#10b981', '#f59e0b', '#ef4444'];

export function PlanBreakdownChart({ data }: { data: { name: string; value: number }[] }) {
  return (
    <ResponsiveContainer width="100%" height={300}>
      <PieChart>
        <Pie
          data={data}
          cx="50%"
          cy="50%"
          outerRadius={100}
          dataKey="value"
          label={({ name, percent }) => `${name} ${(percent * 100).toFixed(0)}%`}
        >
          {data.map((_, i) => <Cell key={i} fill={COLORS[i % COLORS.length]} />)}
        </Pie>
        <Tooltip />
      </PieChart>
    </ResponsiveContainer>
  );
}
```

### 7. Custom tooltip
```tsx
const CustomTooltip = ({ active, payload, label }: any) => {
  if (!active || !payload?.length) return null;
  return (
    <div className="rounded-lg border bg-background p-3 shadow-sm">
      <p className="font-medium">{label}</p>
      {payload.map((p: any, i: number) => (
        <p key={i} style={{ color: p.color }}>{p.name}: {p.value}</p>
      ))}
    </div>
  );
};
// Use in chart: <Tooltip content={<CustomTooltip />} />
```

### 8. Fetch data from a Server Component and pass to the chart
```tsx
// app/dashboard/page.tsx (Server Component)
import { RevenueChart } from '@/components/charts/revenue-chart';
import { db } from '@/lib/db';

export default async function DashboardPage() {
  const data = await db.query.revenue.findMany({ orderBy: (r, { asc }) => [asc(r.month)] });
  return <RevenueChart data={data} />;
}
```
- Always fetch data in Server Components and pass it as props — never fetch inside chart components.

### 9. Theming with Tailwind / shadcn
- Use CSS variables to match your design system:
  ```tsx
  stroke="hsl(var(--primary))" fill="hsl(var(--primary) / 0.15)"
  ```
- If using shadcn/ui, check for the `shadcn/ui charts` primitive (built on Recharts) which adds pre-themed chart wrappers.

### 10. Verify
- Run `npm run dev`.
- Navigate to the page — confirm charts render without hydration errors.
- Resize the browser window to confirm `ResponsiveContainer` makes charts responsive.
- Open DevTools Console — there should be no 'window is not defined' errors.

### Common errors & fixes
- **Hydration mismatch / 'window is not defined'** — A Recharts component is rendering in a Server Component. Add `'use client';` to the chart file or wrap with `dynamic(() => import(...), { ssr: false })`.
- **Chart is invisible / renders at 0 height** — Missing `ResponsiveContainer`, or `ResponsiveContainer` has no `height` prop. Always set a numeric `height`.
- **'Cannot read property of undefined' in tooltip** — The `dataKey` prop doesn't match a field name in the data array. Check spelling.
- **Chart overflows or jumps on first render** — The parent container has no defined size. Add explicit `width`/`height` CSS to the wrapper element.
- **Pie chart labels overlap** — Add `labelLine={false}` and shorten the label, or replace with a separate `Legend` component.
- **TypeScript error on `payload` in custom tooltip** — Type the argument as `any` or import `TooltipProps` from `recharts`.

### What NOT to do
- Do NOT render Recharts components in Server Components — they will throw 'window is not defined'. Always use `'use client'` or `dynamic` with `ssr: false`.
- Do NOT omit `ResponsiveContainer` — charts without it render at 0×0 or overflow their container.
- Do NOT set `width` and `height` directly on the chart element (e.g., `<LineChart width="100%">`) — use `ResponsiveContainer` instead.
- Do NOT fetch data inside chart components — fetch in Server Components and pass data as props.
- Do NOT install `@types/recharts` — types are bundled and the old DefinitelyTyped package is outdated and conflicting.
- Do NOT import all of Recharts with `import * as Recharts` — import only the components you use to keep bundle size small.
